Procedure.description:
Procedure Purpose: FPM RW angular monmentum drift management
Procedure Version: 22 Responsibility: Christian Bihr Last Modified Date: 06.12.2022
History
[CBi 2022/12/06 EUM v. 22.0] edits for AR6290: -inserted dump TC in branches Enable and Disable P.1.A1 and P.1.B1 -inserted case steps P.1.A2 and P.1.B2 and moved the TCs under the true branches (i.e. only execute, if status is different, i.e. send enable TC, when status was disabled) -inserted log message in false branches to inform already enabled or disabled (P.1.A2.B1 and P.1.B2.B1)
Objective
This procedure is used to manage the FPM Reaction Wheels momentum, which allows to drift the RW speed evolution on long term and to delay as much as possible the zero crossing of specific RW speeds.
With this procedure the function can be enabled / disabled, and the FPM drift momentum torque FPM_AJ_wheelMomentumDriftTorque uploaded.
Procedure.title: FPM RW angular monmentum drift management
